<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Treatability study
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a study in which PCB waste is subjected to a treatment process to determine: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Whether the waste is amenable to the treatment process. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) What pretreatment (if any) is required. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The optimal process conditions needed to achieve the desired treatment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The efficiency of a treatment process for the specific type of waste (i.e., soil, sludge, liquid, etc.). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) The characteristics and volumes of residuals from a particular treatment process. A ``treatability study''
is not a mechanism to commercially treat or dispose of PCB waste. Treatment is a form of disposal under this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

