<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
 Use restrictions.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 After July 1, 1986, use of railroad transformers that contain dielectric fluids with a PCB concentration greater
than 1,000 ppm is prohibited. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
 Use in and servicing of mining equipment
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. After January 1, 1982, PCBs may be used in mining equipment only at a concentration level of less than 50 ppm. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
 Use in heat transfer systems.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 After July 1, 1984, PCBs may be used in heat transfer systems only at a concentration level of less than 50 ppm. Heat transfer
systems that were in operation after July 1, 1984 with a concentration level of less than 50 ppm PCBs may be serviced
to maintain a concentration level of less than 50 ppm PCBs. Heat transfer systems may only be serviced with fluids containing
less than 50 ppm PCBs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
 Use in hydraulic systems.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 After July 1, 1984 PCBs may be used in hydraulic systems only at a concentration level of less than 50 ppm. Hydraulic
systems that were in operation after July 1, 1984 with a concentration level of less than 50 ppm PCBs may be serviced
to maintain a concentration level of less than 50 ppm PCBs. Hydraulic systems may only be serviced with fluids containing
less than 50 ppm PCBs. 
