<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) The standard for treatment of PCB remediation wastes where the PCBs have been microencapsulated or vitrified is
less than 50 micrograms PCBs per liter as measured by the Toxicity Characteristic Leaching Procedure (TCLP), 40 CFR
part 261, Appendix II, Method 1311. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
