concentration less than 50 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=6 f=1 -->
m
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
g/l PCB) shall be disposed of at an off-site facility according to paragraph (a)(5)(i)(B)(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
2
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) or (
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
3
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
 Non-porous surfaces
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. Non-porous surfaces shall be decontaminated in accordance with 761.79. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Low exposure areas
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(A)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
 Bulk PCB remediation waste.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The cleanup level for low exposure areas is less than or equal to 25 ppm unless otherwise specified in this paragraph.
Cleanup of bulk PCB remediation waste in low exposure areas shall be accomplished by one or more of the following: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
1
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) Remove and dispose of all materials at concentrations equal to or greater than 25 ppm PCB. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
2
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) Remove and dispose of all materials equal to or greater than 50 ppm PCB if the area is secured by a fence and a sign including
the ML. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
3
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) Remove all materials greater than 100 ppm PCB and place a clean (less than 1 ppm PCBs) soil cover of a uniform thickness
of a minimum of 25 centimeters (10 inches) over the site where PCBs remain in excess of 25 ppm. A cap of other clean impervious
material, including concrete or asphalt at a minimum uniform thickness of 15 centimeters (6 inches) may be used in
place of the clean soil cover. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
4
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
)(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
i
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) Bulk PCB remediation waste may be disposed of onsite using a solvent extraction process where: A non-chlorinated
solvent is used; the solvent extraction process occurs at ambient temperature; the extraction process is not exothermic;
and no external heat is used for the extraction process. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
